-- Enel Green Power, Fiat, Telecom Italia May Move: Italian Equity Preview
-- B y   T o m m a s o   E b h a r d t
-- 2010-11-09T05:00:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-09/enel-green-power-fiat-telecom-italia-may-move-italian-equity-preview.html
The following companies may be
active in Italian trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses and
share prices are from the previous close.  The benchmark  FTSE MIB Index  gained 34.24, or 0.2 percent,
to 21,228.98 in Milan.  Enel Green Power SpA  (EGPW IM): Enel SpA’s alternative-
energy unit said third-quarter net income rose 27 percent to 99
million euros ($137 million). The shares dropped 1.6 percent to
1.57 euros.  Fiat SpA  (F IM): Chief Executive Officer Sergio Marchionne
ruled out a spinoff of Fiat’s Mirafiori plant in Italy or
Chrysler Group LLC getting a stake in the plant.  Fiat shares were unchanged at 12.78 euros.  Impregilo SpA (IPG IM): Italy’s largest construction
company’s nine-month net income rose to 108.8 million euros from
32.36 million euros a year earlier. Impregilo gained 1 percent,
to 2.27 euros.  Telecom Italia SpA  (TIT IM): Italy’s biggest phone company
agreed with Bolivia’s government and Entel Bolivia “ending the
controversy that arose in 2007 following the expropriation” of
a stake held by a unit of the Italian company in Entel.  Telecom Italia lost 1.1 percent to 1.025 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tommaso Ebhardt in Milan at 
